msgid "Opens the :ref:`svg_source_editor`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:146
msgid "Opens the :ref:`glyph_palette`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:147
msgid "Dialogs"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:147
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:251
msgid "Glyph Palette"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:150
msgid ""
"These buttons allow converting a selected text. Said conversion functions "
"are also available as shortcut actions under \"Interaction Tool\" in the "
"shortcut preferences."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:153
msgid ""
"Converts text so that it does not wrap automatically. In addition, the "
"CSS :ref:`text_property_white_space` collapse rule is applied so that any "
"hidden white space is removed, and the rule is switched so that additional "
"white spaces are not removed. Any absolute SVG 1.1 character transforms are "
"changed to become new lines."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:156
msgid ""
"Converts text so that it wraps around a maximum inline length (width for "
"horizontal text, and height for vertical text). As "
"with :guilabel:`Preformatted`, the CSS :ref:`text_property_white_space` rule "
"and character transforms are processed to create line breaks and avoid the "
"collapse of additional white spaces."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:159
msgid ""
"Converts text to SVG 1.1 style text, where "
"additional :ref:`text_property_white_space` get collapsed and new lines are "
"positioned absolutely. This is how previous versions of Krita handled text, "
"as well as the dominant way to handle SVG text. Use this to prepare text for "
"export when the end result should show in a SVG 1.1 compatible renderer."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:161
msgid "Convert Type..."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:161
msgid ""
"Text in shape and text on path are not among the conversion options. "
"Instead, use :guilabel:`Flow Text in Shape` and :guilabel:`Put Text On Path` "
"from the rightclick menu in the :ref:`shape_selection_tool_text`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:168
msgid ""
"This mode enables on-canvas text styling for a number of text properties."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:172
msgid ".. image:: /images/text/type-setting-mode.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:172
msgid ""
"Text in Type Setting Mode, with \"Setting\" selected, and the cursor "
"hovering over the :guilabel:`Font Size` metric line."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:174
msgid ""
"When enabled, the selection will be replaced with a number of metric lines. "
"When there's no selection, these lines are drawn for the paragraph, and uses "
"the paragraph's font metrics, while with a selection, it will use the "
"selected glyphs font metrics as retrieved during the text layout."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:176
msgid ""
"Hovering over the lines will highlight them, and show the name of the "
"relevant metric. |mouseleft| :kbd:`+ drag` on these lines will increase or "
"decrease the size of this metric. This "
"way, :ref:`text_property_font_size`, :ref:`text_property_line_height` "
"and :ref:`text_property_baseline_shift` can be modified directly on canvas. "
"Pressing :kbd:`Shift` will display a different set of metrics: "
"the :ref:`text_property_baseline`. Clicking a baseline will "
"set :ref:`text_property_dominant_baseline` "
"and :ref:`text_property_alignment_baseline` to that baseline, allowing the "
"alignment of text of different sizes to said baseline."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:180
msgid ".. image:: /images/text/type-setting-mode-baselines.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:180
msgid ""
"The alternate baseline mode. Cursor is hovering over the :guilabel:`Hanging` "
"baseline."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:182
msgid ""
"When text is :guilabel:`Preformatted` or :guilabel:`Pre-positioned`, two "
"additional controls are visible at the start and end of a selection. These "
"allow modifying the position and rotation of each cluster. The square handle "
"allows moving the whole selection, while the round handle scales and rotates "
"the selection. There's a series of actions for moving the square handle "
"available in the shortcuts configuration for the text tool. These (for each "
"direction) :guilabel:`Move Text Selection Down By 1 Pixel`, and will move "
"the selected text in the given direction. There's also :guilabel:`Remove "
"Character Transforms` which will remove all character transforms, (relative, "
"absolute and rotation) from the given range."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:186
msgid ".. image:: /images/text/type-setting-mode-handle-adjust.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:186
msgid ""
"The selected word has been rotated by |mouseleft| + dragging the handles."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:190
msgid ""
"For fine-tuned typographic adjustments, like manual kerning, it's "
"recommended to use these two handles over "
"CSS :ref:`text_property_letter_spacing`. The latter is intended for spacing "
"letters over a whole chunk of text, and implemented in subtly different ways "
"in every implementation."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:192
msgid ""
"Internally, these modify SVG 1.1 relative character transforms, which means "
"they don't break the shaping, and are supported in all the major browsers."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:197
msgid "SVG Source Editor"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:199
msgid ""
"A small window to directly edit the SVG source of the text. The text layout "
"is capable of more complex text than the text tool can edit on-canvas. If "
"you are familiar with SVG, you will be able to edit it directly and use "
"powerful features like "
"nested :ref:`text_property_baseline_shift`, :ref:`text_property_text_decoration` "
"and :ref:`text_property_direction`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:202
msgid ".. image:: /images/tools/Text-editor-example.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:203
msgid "Editing"
msgstr "編集"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:205
msgid ""
"Press :guilabel:`Save` as you're done with your edits to preview them on "
"canvas."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`保存` を押せばこれまでにした編集をキャンバス上に反映できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:208
msgid "Save :kbd:`Ctrl + S`"
msgstr "保存 :kbd:`Ctrl + S`"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:209
msgid "Save current edits to the text on canvas."
msgstr "テキストにされた編集をキャンバスに保存する。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:211
msgid "File"
msgstr "ファイル"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:211
msgid "Close :kbd:`Ctrl + W`"
msgstr "閉じる :kbd:`Ctrl + W`"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:211
msgid "Close the editor."
msgstr "エディタを閉じます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:214
msgid "Basic editing functions:"
msgstr "基本的な編集機能:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:216
msgid "Undo :kbd:`Ctrl + Z`"
msgstr "元に戻す :kbd:`Ctrl + Z`"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:217
msgid "Undo the last action in the text editor."
msgstr "テキストエディタで最後にした動作を元に戻します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:218
msgid "Redo :kbd:`Ctrl + Shift + Z`"
msgstr "やり直し :kbd:`Ctrl + Shift + Z`"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:219
msgid "Redo the last undone action in the text editor."
msgstr "テキストエディタで最後に元に戻した動作をやり直します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:220
msgid "Cut :kbd:`Ctrl + X`"
msgstr "切り取り :kbd:`Ctrl + X`"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:221
msgid "Cut selected text to the clipboard."
msgstr "選択されたテキストをクリップボードに切り取ります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/text.rst:222
